HOUSE BILL No. 1046
A BILL FOR AN ACT to amend the Indiana Code concerning
courts and court officers and to make an appropriation.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
1 SECTION 1. IC 4-12-16.2-5, AS ADDED BY P.L.201-2023,
2 SECTION 70, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
3 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 5. The following accounts are established within
4 the fund:
5 (1) The state unrestricted opioid settlement account. The account
6 consists of money distributed to the account under
7 IC 4-6-15-4(a)(1) and any interest earnings that accrue to the fund
8 under section 7 of this chapter. Expenditures from the account
9 may be made only after appropriation of the money in the account
10 by the general assembly. Money in the account must be used by
11 the state for oversight and administration of programs for
12 treatment, education, recovery, and prevention of opioid use
13 disorder and any co-occurring substance use disorders or mental
14 health issues. Money in the account may be used for the
15 funding of family recovery courts and safe baby courts (as
16 defined in IC 33-23-16-9.5) under IC 33-23-16.5.
17 (2) The state abatement opioid settlement account. The account
