13 SECTION 2. IC 33-23-16.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
14 AS A NEW CHAPTER TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
15 JULY 1, 2026]:
16 Chapter 16.5. Family Recovery Court Fund
17 Sec. 1. As used in this chapter, "family recovery court" means
18 a court that:
19 (1) targets cases of abuse or neglect wherein a parent or
20 primary caregiver suffers from a substance use disorder or
21 co-occurring disorders; and
22 (2) is certified as a problem solving court under
23 IC 33-23-16-17 by the office of judicial administration.
24 Sec. 2. The family recovery court fund is established to carry
25 out the purpose of funding family recovery courts and safe baby
26 courts (as defined in IC 33-23-16-9.5) under IC 33-23-16.
27 Sec. 3. The office of judicial administration shall administer the
28 fund.
29 Sec. 4. The expenses of administering the fund shall be paid
30 from money in the fund.
31 Sec. 5. The fund consists of the following:
32 (1) Money appropriated by the general assembly from the
33 state unrestricted opioid settlement account established under
34 IC 4-12-16.2-5(1).
35 (2) Donations, gifts, and money received from any other
36 source, including transfers from other funds or accounts.
37 Sec. 6. Money in the fund is continuously appropriated for the
38 purpose of the fund.
39 Sec. 7. The treasurer of state shall invest the money in the fund
40 not currently needed to meet the obligations of the fund in the same
41 manner as other public money may be invested. Interest that
42 accrues from the investments shall be deposited in the fund.
